- Objective: Deploy an apache server using ConfigMap to serer custom web content
- Task details
   - create a new project named: 'peech'
   - create a new application using the 'Bitnami's Apache' image
   - create a firl named 'index.html' with the content 'Apche Rocks'
   - using a ConfigMap named 'content' configure the Apache server to serve the 'index.html' file to its user
   - Make the application accessible via the URL "http://apache.app-crc.testing"
Hint: The document root for the apche server is "/app"

oc new-project peech

create the application
oc new-app bitnami/apache
oc get pods
echo "Apache Rocks" > index.html

create a ConfigMap named content from the file
oc create configmap content --from-file=index.html

check the deployment name
oc get deployment

edit the deployment
oc edit deployment apache

add volume
-------------
volumes:
  - name: content
    configMap:
       name: content

Add volume mounts
----------------------
volumeMounts:
  - name: content
    mountPath: /app/index.html
    subPath: index.html

expose the service
----------------------
oc expose service apache

oc get route
oc edit route apache
spec:
  host: apache.app-crc.testing

